    {
      "id": "fa00c8089e40124c8d707aac3dea852e57a17569",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-06-07 23:06:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nThomas, it would be good if you, or someone else from CEA that is familiar with ChangeLog, could review this patch.\n\nAFAIK, the reason the rename record was split into two parts is because of DNE.  The rename may happen across multiple MDTs, and the two parts of the rename were thought to appear in different MDT ChangeLogs.\n\nI suspect that a single rename record on the master MDT is enough, since it should always cause the same sequence of operations on the objects (regardless of which MDT/OST they are located on), it avoids complexity in linking up the two parts of the rename on the MDTs, and if the target filesystem does not have DNE at all it avoids extra complexity that is irrelevant on the target.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
